{"type":"message","id":"caa328e9","parentId":"c30f832f","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:46:22.664Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_1uosxynr7b2k_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md\r\n---\r\n## Pending\r\n- [ ] Hybrid CFIxFreq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n  - Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n  - Test: does this distinguish \"constant format\" (freq�160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)?\r\n  - Run: 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\r\n\r\n## Key Insights from This Session\r\n\r\n1. **CFI and frequency are ORTHOGONAL signals** - combine both, don't choose one\r\n2. **Constant-format tokens** (freq=160, CFI=1) are the trap - they look causal but aren't\r\n3. **Three-dimensional compression filter**: CFI � 0.5 AND freq � 3 AND freq < 120\r\n4. **Compression objective for Layer 1 is now concrete**: score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n---\r\n## Hybrid CFIxFreq Scoring Experiment (Strategy C) ?\r\n- **Formula implemented:** `score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)`\r\n- **Hypothesis:** Distinguishes \"constant format\" (freq�160, CFI�1, score�1.0) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5, score varies)\r\n- **Test:** 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare hybrid scores against binary thresholds\r\n- **Analysis script:** `research/hybrid_scoring_analysis.ps1`\r\n\r\n## Key Insights from This Session\r\n\r\n1. **CFI and frequency are ORTHOGONAL signals** - combine both, don't choose one\r\n2. **Constant-format tokens** (freq=160, CFI=1) are the trap - they look causal but aren't\r\n3. **Three-dimensional compression filter**: CFI � 0.5 AND freq � 3 AND freq < 120\r\n4. **Compression objective for Layer 1 is now concrete**: score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n5. **Hybrid scoring provides soft thresholding**: avoids hard boundary problems of binary filters"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":817,"aggregated":"research/CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md\r\n---\r\n## Pending\r\n- [ ] Hybrid CFIxFreq scoring experiment (Strategy C)\r\n  - Formula: score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n  - Test: does this distinguish \"constant format\" (freq�160, CFI=1) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5)?\r\n  - Run: 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare against binary thresholds\r\n\r\n## Key Insights from This Session\r\n\r\n1. **CFI and frequency are ORTHOGONAL signals** - combine both, don't choose one\r\n2. **Constant-format tokens** (freq=160, CFI=1) are the trap - they look causal but aren't\r\n3. **Three-dimensional compression filter**: CFI � 0.5 AND freq � 3 AND freq < 120\r\n4. **Compression objective for Layer 1 is now concrete**: score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n---\r\n## Hybrid CFIxFreq Scoring Experiment (Strategy C) ?\r\n- **Formula implemented:** `score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)`\r\n- **Hypothesis:** Distinguishes \"constant format\" (freq�160, CFI�1, score�1.0) from \"research trajectory\" (freq<120, CFI>0.5, score varies)\r\n- **Test:** 200 pulses, 80/20 split, compare hybrid scores against binary thresholds\r\n- **Analysis script:** `research/hybrid_scoring_analysis.ps1`\r\n\r\n## Key Insights from This Session\r\n\r\n1. **CFI and frequency are ORTHOGONAL signals** - combine both, don't choose one\r\n2. **Constant-format tokens** (freq=160, CFI=1) are the trap - they look causal but aren't\r\n3. **Three-dimensional compression filter**: CFI � 0.5 AND freq � 3 AND freq < 120\r\n4. **Compression objective for Layer 1 is now concrete**: score(T) = CFI(T) x min(1, freq(T)/120)\r\n5. **Hybrid scoring provides soft thresholding**: avoids hard boundary problems of binary filters","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774377982662}}
