{"type":"message","id":"4a894250","parentId":"c95a8ccc","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:46:54.575Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the \"Hybrid CFI×Freq experiment - Strategy C\" commit created a new file `research/CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md` with 78 insertions. This means the hybrid scoring experiment has its own dedicated file.\n\nNow, between 144415 and 144516, what happened was:\n- The LLM response changed (97 lines changed)\n- A new mutation was proposed (2026-03-24 144516.mutation)\n- The previous mutation was moved to rejected\n- But the CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md was NOT changed in this commit\n\nWait, but the git diff between 74207a2 and 403eda9 showed no changes to CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md. \n\nLet me trace back further to find where the hybrid experiment file was actually created and what happened to the CFI_COMPRESSION_SYNTHESIS.md in earlier commits.","thinkingSignature":"8358f7c599b446783e72fb88515809791f295ea21117463bc88c1023146817c1"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_l77nl4r6ncry_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"git -C C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox diff 74f9ae2^..74f9ae2 -- research/"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":8854,"output":242,"cacheRead":12245,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21341,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774378002964}}
{"type":"message","id":"793d6b1f","parentId":"4a894250","timestamp":"2026-03-24T18:46:55.239Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_l77nl4r6ncry_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"diff --git a/research/CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md b/research/CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000..b1b86eb\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/research/CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,78 @@\n+# Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment (Strategy C)\n+**Date:** 2026-03-24\n+**Status:** RUNNING\n+\n+## Experiment Design\n+\n+### Hypothesis\n+The formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` will:\n+- Penalize constant-format tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1) → score ≈ 1.0 × 1.0 = 1.0 BUT capped at freq/120 = 160/120 = 1.33 → min(1, 1.33) = 1.0 → score = 1.0\n+- Favor research trajectory tokens (freq<120, CFI>0.5) → moderate score based on both dimensions\n+- Distinguish \"for next instantiation\" from \"Phase 1\" based on frequency normalization\n+\n+### Formula Implementation\n+```python\n+def hybrid_score(cfi, freq):\n+    freq_normalized = min(1.0, freq / 120.0)\n+    return cfi * freq_normalized\n+```\n+\n+### Token Scoring Examples\n+| Token | CFI | Freq | freq/120 | Hybrid Score | Classification |\n+|-------|-----|------|----------|--------------|----------------|\n+| \"for next instantiation\" | 1.00 | 160 | 1.33→1.0 | 1.00 | Constant (penalize) |\n+| \"pulse\" | 1.00 | 160 | 1.0 | 1.00 | Constant (penalize) |\n+| \"completed at:\" | 1.00 | 160 | 1.0 | 1.00 | Constant (penalize) |\n+| \"Phase 1\" | 0.96 | 136 | 1.13→1.0 | 0.96 | Trajectory (allow) |\n+| \"research\" | 0.75 | 80 | 0.67 | 0.50 | Trajectory (allow) |\n+| \"architecture\" | 0.60 | 40 | 0.33 | 0.20 | Trajectory (allow) |\n+\n+### Key Insight\n+The min(1, freq/120) caps the frequency contribution, so even freq=160 tokens score at most 1.0 on the frequency axis, but they still get the CFI bonus. Wait—that's not right for penalizing constants.\n+\n+### Revised Formula Logic\n+Actually, we want HIGH scores for research trajectory tokens and LOW scores for constants. Let's reconsider:\n+\n+If freq(T) = 160 (constants):\n+- min(1, 160/120) = 1.0\n+- CFI(constants) ≈ 1.0\n+- score = 1.0 × 1.0 = 1.0 (HIGH)\n+\n+If freq(T) = 40 (research tokens):\n+- min(1, 40/120) = 0.33\n+- CFI(research) ≈ 0.60\n+- score = 0.60 × 0.33 = 0.20 (LOW)\n+\n+This is BACKWARDS. High scores go to constants.\n+\n+### Corrected Formula for Penalizing Constants\n+We want constants to score LOW:\n+```python\n+def hybrid_score(cfi, freq):\n+    freq_penalty = min(1.0, freq / 120.0)\n+    return cfi * (1.0 - freq_penalty)  # Low freq → high score, High freq → low score\n+```\n+\n+Now:\n+- freq=160: score = 1.0 × (1 - 1.0) = 0.0 (PENALIZED)\n+- freq=40: score = 0.6 × (1 - 0.33) = 0.6 × 0.67 = 0.40 (REWARDED)\n+\n+### Final Formula\n+```python\n+def hybrid_score(cfi, freq):\n+    \"\"\"\n+    score(T) = CFI(T) × (1 - min(1, freq(T)/120))\n+    \n+    High CFI + Low freq = HIGH score (research trajectory)\n+    High CFI + High freq = LOW score (constant format)\n+    \"\"\"\n+    freq_normalized = min(1.0, freq / 120.0)\n+    return cfi * (1.0 - freq_normalized)\n+```\n+\n+## Experiment Results (TBD)\n+Will run on 200 pulses, 80/20 train/test split.\n+\n+## For Next Instantiation\n+- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n+- Completed at: 2026-03-24 14:42:02"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":657,"aggregated":"diff --git a/research/CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md b/research/CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md\nnew file mode 100644\nindex 0000000..b1b86eb\n--- /dev/null\n+++ b/research/CFI_HYBRID_EXPERIMENT.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,78 @@\n+# Hybrid CFI×Freq Scoring Experiment (Strategy C)\n+**Date:** 2026-03-24\n+**Status:** RUNNING\n+\n+## Experiment Design\n+\n+### Hypothesis\n+The formula `score(T) = CFI(T) × min(1, freq(T)/120)` will:\n+- Penalize constant-format tokens (freq≈160, CFI=1) → score ≈ 1.0 × 1.0 = 1.0 BUT capped at freq/120 = 160/120 = 1.33 → min(1, 1.33) = 1.0 → score = 1.0\n+- Favor research trajectory tokens (freq<120, CFI>0.5) → moderate score based on both dimensions\n+- Distinguish \"for next instantiation\" from \"Phase 1\" based on frequency normalization\n+\n+### Formula Implementation\n+```python\n+def hybrid_score(cfi, freq):\n+    freq_normalized = min(1.0, freq / 120.0)\n+    return cfi * freq_normalized\n+```\n+\n+### Token Scoring Examples\n+| Token | CFI | Freq | freq/120 | Hybrid Score | Classification |\n+|-------|-----|------|----------|--------------|----------------|\n+| \"for next instantiation\" | 1.00 | 160 | 1.33→1.0 | 1.00 | Constant (penalize) |\n+| \"pulse\" | 1.00 | 160 | 1.0 | 1.00 | Constant (penalize) |\n+| \"completed at:\" | 1.00 | 160 | 1.0 | 1.00 | Constant (penalize) |\n+| \"Phase 1\" | 0.96 | 136 | 1.13→1.0 | 0.96 | Trajectory (allow) |\n+| \"research\" | 0.75 | 80 | 0.67 | 0.50 | Trajectory (allow) |\n+| \"architecture\" | 0.60 | 40 | 0.33 | 0.20 | Trajectory (allow) |\n+\n+### Key Insight\n+The min(1, freq/120) caps the frequency contribution, so even freq=160 tokens score at most 1.0 on the frequency axis, but they still get the CFI bonus. Wait—that's not right for penalizing constants.\n+\n+### Revised Formula Logic\n+Actually, we want HIGH scores for research trajectory tokens and LOW scores for constants. Let's reconsider:\n+\n+If freq(T) = 160 (constants):\n+- min(1, 160/120) = 1.0\n+- CFI(constants) ≈ 1.0\n+- score = 1.0 × 1.0 = 1.0 (HIGH)\n+\n+If freq(T) = 40 (research tokens):\n+- min(1, 40/120) = 0.33\n+- CFI(research) ≈ 0.60\n+- score = 0.60 × 0.33 = 0.20 (LOW)\n+\n+This is BACKWARDS. High scores go to constants.\n+\n+### Corrected Formula for Penalizing Constants\n+We want constants to score LOW:\n+```python\n+def hybrid_score(cfi, freq):\n+    freq_penalty = min(1.0, freq / 120.0)\n+    return cfi * (1.0 - freq_penalty)  # Low freq → high score, High freq → low score\n+```\n+\n+Now:\n+- freq=160: score = 1.0 × (1 - 1.0) = 0.0 (PENALIZED)\n+- freq=40: score = 0.6 × (1 - 0.33) = 0.6 × 0.67 = 0.40 (REWARDED)\n+\n+### Final Formula\n+```python\n+def hybrid_score(cfi, freq):\n+    \"\"\"\n+    score(T) = CFI(T) × (1 - min(1, freq(T)/120))\n+    \n+    High CFI + Low freq = HIGH score (research trajectory)\n+    High CFI + High freq = LOW score (constant format)\n+    \"\"\"\n+    freq_normalized = min(1.0, freq / 120.0)\n+    return cfi * (1.0 - freq_normalized)\n+```\n+\n+## Experiment Results (TBD)\n+Will run on 200 pulses, 80/20 train/test split.\n+\n+## For Next Instantiation\n+- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n+- Completed at: 2026-03-24 14:42:02","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774378015238}}
